@startuml svc-guest-profiles--post-guests

!include ../theme.puml
skinparam sequence {
    ArrowColor #7c3aed
}

header [[/microservices/svc-guest-profiles/#integration-context ⬆ svc-guest-profiles Integration Context]]

title POST /guests\nCreate guest profile\n<size:10><color:#7c3aed>ARCHITECT OVERRIDE — enriched with identity verification gate and event emission</color></size>

participant "Client" as Client [[/applications/]]
participant "svc-guest-profiles" as Svc [[/microservices/svc-guest-profiles/]] #EDE9FE
participant "IDVerify" as IDV #F3E8FF
participant "Kafka" as Kafka [[/architecture/events/]] #F5F3FF
database "PostgreSQL" as DB [[/microservices/svc-guest-profiles/#data-store]] #FEF9C3

note over Svc
  [[/services/api/svc-guest-profiles.html View in Swagger UI]]
  **Single source of truth for guest identity**
  All services resolve guest data through this API.
  No shadow guest records permitted (ADR principle).
end note

Client -> Svc : POST /guests\n{ first_name, last_name,\nemail, phone, date_of_birth,\nemergency_contact }
activate Svc #7c3aed

note right of Svc : Validate required fields\nCheck email uniqueness\nNormalize phone format

Svc -> DB : SELECT id FROM guests\nWHERE email = :email
activate DB #FEF9C3
DB --> Svc : Result (0 or 1 rows)
deactivate DB

alt Email already registered
    Svc --> Client : 409 Conflict\n(email_already_exists,\nexisting_guest_id)
else New guest
    Svc -> IDV : Verify identity\n(name, DOB, document)
    activate IDV #F3E8FF
    IDV --> Svc : Verification result\n(verified: true/false, score)
    deactivate IDV

    Svc -> DB : INSERT INTO guests\n(profile fields,\nverification_status,\ncreated_at)
    activate DB #FEF9C3
    DB --> Svc : guest_id
    deactivate DB

    Svc ->> Kafka : guest.profile.created\n(guest_id, email, tier = NEW)

    Svc --> Client : 201 Created\n(guest_id, verification_status)
    deactivate Svc
end

@enduml
